Because a <b>geometric sequence</b> is a sequence where each term after the first is found by multiplying the previous one by a fixed non-zero number called the ratio of the sequence, and because each term is an integer, the common ratio has to be an integer. So we factor out 2009. We also know we must have <b>two factors</b> of 2009.  We see that $2009=1+ 7^2 +41^2=37*59$, and we see the two integers <b>37</b> and <b>59</b> <b>are possible for</b> $a$ and $b$ in <b>order</b>. Because $a<b<2009$, we see that <b>$a=37$</b> is the correct <b>answer</b>;
However, $59$ works too because $a<b<2009$. (In order to see that, $a=59$, $b=343$, and $2009=343*7^2$).


